        "caption": "TABLE II: Architecture of LSTM model used to detect anomaly detection",
        "table": "<table id=\"S4.T2.1\" class=\"ltx_tabular ltx_centering ltx_align_middle\">\n<tr id=\"S4.T2.1.1\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.1.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T2.1.1.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\">Layers</span></td>\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.1.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\"><span id=\"S4.T2.1.1.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\">Hyper-parameters</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S4.T2.1.2\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.2.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">LSTM Layer</td>\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.2.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Neurons: 128</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S4.T2.1.3\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.3.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Activation</td>\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.3.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">ReLU</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S4.T2.1.4\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.4.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">LSTM Layer</td>\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.4.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Neurons: 64</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S4.T2.1.5\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.5.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Activation</td>\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.5.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">ReLU</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S4.T2.1.6\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.6.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Dense Layer</td>\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.6.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Neurons: 21</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S4.T2.1.7\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.7.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Activation</td>\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.7.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Softmax</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S4.T2.1.8\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.8.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Loss</td>\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.8.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Categorical crossentropy</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S4.T2.1.9\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.9.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Epochs</td>\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.9.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S4.T2.1.10\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.10.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">Batch size</td>\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.10.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_t\">1024</td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"S4.T2.1.11\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.11.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_b ltx_border_t\">Optimizer</td>\n<td id=\"S4.T2.1.11.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_border_b ltx_border_t\">Adam</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n",
        "footnotes": "",
        "references": [
            "Regarding the DL model used in Fedstellar during the experiments, it was an LSTM network. Specifically, it was a two-layer LSTM network consisting of an input layer, two hidden layers, and an output layer. The first hidden layer has 128 neurons, while the second has 64 neurons. The output layer was a dense network with 21 neurons. The chosen activation function for the hidden layers was ReLU, and for the output layer, Softmax was employed. As a result, the output provides the probability for each of the considered classes. Finally, the batch size was set to 1024, and both rounds and epochs were fixed to 10. Table II summarizes the architecture of the DL model. This work did not consider carrying out a grid or random search to find the optimal hyper-parameters since this work aims to probe the feasibility of Fedstellar to detect anomalies in an industrial setting, not to find the best DL model."
        ]
    },
